SIMPLE: toboggan
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Toboggan
<hw>To*bog"gan</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Corruption of
American Indian <ets>odabagan</ets> a sled.]</ety> <def>A kind of sledge
made of pliable board, turned up at one or both ends, used for coasting
down hills or prepared inclined planes; also, a sleigh or sledge, to be
drawn by dogs, or by hand, over soft and deep snow.</def>
<altsp>[Written also <asp>tobogan</asp>, and
<asp>tarbogan</asp>.]</altsp>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Toboggan</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Toboggan
<hw>To*bog"gan</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. &
p. p.</pos> <conjf>Tobogganed</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb.
n.</pos> <conjf>Tobogganing</conjf>.]</vmorph> <def>To slide down hill
over the snow or ice on a toboggan.</def>
<rj><au>Barilett.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Tobogganist</ent>⟦br⟧
<ent>Tobogganer</ent>⟦br⟧
